bytes.body:
Arbitrum Optimism enables seamless bridging of assets between L1 and L2 using AggLayer. To migrate assets, deploy the AggLayer contract, and call `deposit()` to transfer assets from L1 to L2. On the L2 side, use the `zkEVM` to optimize execution of the `deposit()` function. To verify the migration, query the `balanceOf()` function on the AggLayer contract. For example, using the Arbitrum SDK in JavaScript:

const { AggLayer } = require('@arbitrum/sdk);
const aggLayer = new AggLayer('contractAddress');
const balance = await aggLayer.balanceOf('assetAddress');
console.log(`Balance: ${balance}`);

